      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0405P0-05259'>
        <a name='S6CV0405P0_20030522_WH_125'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-christopher-chope' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0405P0_20030522_WH_125' title='Link to this speech by Mr Christopher Chope' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-christopher-chope" title="Mr Christopher Chope">Mr. Chope</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            I shall not give way at the moment, as I want to make progress. The hon. Gentleman has made
            
            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_361wh' title='Col. 361WH &mdash; HC Deb 22 May 2003 vol 405 c361WH' name='column_361wh' href='#column_361wh' rel='bookmark'>361WH</a>
            some important points. As he said, we have much in common. I wish to re-emphasise his point on the revenue shortfall. It is clear from the evidence of London First that, when the scheme was set up, net revenue of &#x00A3;250 million a year was expected. Just before the scheme began, it was estimated that there would be net revenue of &#x00A3;150 million. It appears that the figure will be far less than that, and it will be dwarfed by the subsidy that is already going into London buses.
          </p>
